     1→# Tailwind CSS + Astro + Vue 3 Best Practices (2024-2025)
     2→
     3→**Research Date:** 2025-10-22
     4→**Focus:** Configuration architecture, animations, SSR patterns, plugin design
     5→
     6→---
     7→
     8→## Executive Summary
     9→
    10→Tailwind CSS v4 introduced major architectural changes that fundamentally alter configuration patterns. The shift from `tailwind.config.js` to CSS-first configuration via `@theme` directive provides cleaner theme management, better type safety, and simplified multi-theme implementations. Astro + Vue 3 integration benefits from these patterns through improved SSR safety and hydration management.
    11→
    12→**Key Findings:**
    13→- Tailwind v4 uses `@theme` directive in CSS files instead of JavaScript config
    14→- `darkMode: "selector"` (v3) becomes `darkMode: "class"` for Astro SSR compatibility
    15→- Animation systems should centralize tokens via `@theme` with JavaScript/Vue integration via CSS variables
    16→- Custom utilities via `@utility` directive preferred over full plugins for most cases
    17→- Astro View Transitions require special dark mode persistence patterns
    18→
    19→---
    20→
    21→## 1. Tailwind Config Architecture
    22→
    23→### v4 Paradigm Shift: CSS-First Configuration
    24→
    25→**Source:** https://tailwindcss.com/docs/theme
    26→
    27→Tailwind v4 eliminates `tailwind.config.js` in favor of CSS-based configuration using the `@theme` directive.
    28→
    29→#### `@theme` Directive Fundamentals
    30→
    31→**Core difference from `:root`:**
    32→- `@theme` variables generate utility classes AND create CSS variables
    33→- `:root` variables are purely stylistic (no utilities generated)
    34→- Use `@theme` for design tokens, `:root` for internal CSS-only values
    35→
    36→**Theme Variable Namespaces:**
    37→
    38→| Namespace | Generated Utilities | Example |
    39→|-----------|-------------------|---------|
    40→| `--color-*` | `bg-`, `text-`, `border-`, `fill-` | `--color-primary: #3f3cbb` |
    41→| `--font-*` | `font-sans`, `font-serif` | `--font-display: Poppins, sans-serif` |
    42→| `--spacing-*` | `px-`, `py-`, `gap-`, `max-h-` | `--spacing-7: 1.75rem` |
    43→| `--radius-*` | `rounded-sm`, `rounded-lg` | `--radius-xl: 1rem` |
    44→| `--shadow-*` | `shadow-md`, `shadow-lg` | `--shadow-brutal: 4px 4px 0 #000` |
    45→| `--breakpoint-*` | `sm:*`, `md:*`, `lg:*` | `--breakpoint-tablet: 48rem` |
    46→
    47→#### Configuration Patterns
    48→
    49→**1. Extending Default Theme (Recommended for Most Cases):**
    50→
    51→```css
    52→@import "tailwindcss";
    53→
    54→@theme {
    55→  /* Adds to existing colors, doesn't replace */
    56→  --color-brand-primary: #3f3cbb;
    57→  --color-brand-secondary: #f59e0b;
    58→
    59→  /* Custom font families */
    60→  --font-display: Poppins, sans-serif;
    61→  --font-body: Inter, system-ui, sans-serif;
    62→
    63→  /* Custom spacing tokens */
    64→  --spacing-18: 4.5rem;
    65→  --spacing-128: 32rem;
    66→}
    67→```
    68→
    69→**2. Overriding Default Values:**
    70→
    71→```css
    72→@theme {
    73→  /* Changes existing breakpoint */
    74→  --breakpoint-sm: 30rem; /* was 40rem */
    75→
    76→  /* Replaces default shadow */
    77→  --shadow-xl: 0 20px 25px -5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    78→}
    79→```
    80→
    81→**3. Complete Namespace Replacement:**
    82→
    83→```css
    84→@theme {
    85→  /* Remove ALL default colors */
    86→  --color-*: initial;
    87→
    88→  /* Define only your custom palette */
    89→  --color-primary: #3f3cbb;
    90→  --color-secondary: #f59e0b;
    91→  --color-neutral-50: #fafafa;
    92→  --color-neutral-900: #171717;
    93→}
    94→```
    95→
    96→**⚠️ Warning:** Complete replacement removes utility classes like `bg-red-500`, `text-blue-600`, etc.
    97→
    98→#### Advanced Techniques
    99→
   100→**Referencing Other Variables:**
   101→
   102→```css
   103→@theme inline {
   104→  /* inline option prevents CSS variable resolution issues */
   105→  --font-sans: var(--font-inter);
   106→  --color-accent: var(--color-brand-primary);
   107→}
   108→```
   109→
   110→**Animation Keyframes in @theme:**
   111→
   112→```css
   113→@theme {
   114→  --animate-fade-in: fade-in 0.3s ease-out;
   115→  --animate-slide-up: slide-up 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
   116→
   117→  @keyframes fade-in {
   118→    from { opacity: 0; }
   119→    to { opacity: 1; }
   120→  }
   121→
   122→  @keyframes slide-up {
   123→    from { transform: translateY(1rem); opacity: 0; }
   124→    to { transform: translateY(0); opacity: 1; }
   125→  }
   126→}
   127→```
   128→
   129→**Sharing Across Projects (Monorepo Pattern):**
   130→
   131→```css
   132→/* packages/design-tokens/theme.css */
   133→@theme {
   134→  --color-brand-primary: #3f3cbb;
   135→  --color-brand-secondary: #f59e0b;
   136→  /* ... all shared tokens */
   137→}
   138→
   139→/* apps/marketing/styles/global.css */
   140→@import "@company/design-tokens/theme.css";
   141→@import "tailwindcss";
   142→```
   143→
   144→---
   145→
   146→## 2. Custom Color Palette Organization
   147→
   148→### Semantic Naming with Dark Mode Support
   149→
   150→**Source:** https://simonswiss.com/posts/tailwind-v4-multi-theme
   151→
   152→Tailwind v4 drastically simplifies multi-theme implementation by eliminating the need for RGB channel workarounds required in v3.
   153→
   154→#### v3 vs v4 Comparison
   155→
   156→**v3 Pattern (Complex, Error-Prone):**
   157→```javascript
   158→// tailwind.config.js
   159→module.exports = {
   160→  theme: {
   161→    colors: {
   162→      primary: 'rgb(var(--color-primary) / <alpha-value>)',
   163→    }
   164→  }
   165→}
   166→```
   167→```css
   168→:root {
   169→  --color-primary: 59 130 246; /* RGB channels only */
   170→}
   171→```
   172→
   173→**v4 Pattern (Simple, Intuitive):**
   174→```css
   175→@theme {
   176→  --color-primary: #3b82f6; /* Any valid color format */
   177→}
   178→```
   179→
   180→#### Multi-Theme Architecture
   181→
   182→**Base Theme Definition:**
   183→```css
   184→@import "tailwindcss";
   185→
   186→@theme {
   187→  /* Default/light theme colors */
   188→  --color-background: #ffffff;
   189→  --color-foreground: #171717;
   190→  --color-primary: #3f3cbb;
   191→  --color-secondary: #f59e0b;
   192→  --color-accent: #ec4899;
   193→  --color-muted: #f5f5f5;
   194→  --color-border: #e5e5e5;
   195→}
   196→```
   197→
   198→**Theme Variants:**
   199→```css
   200→@layer base {
   201→  /* Dark mode */
   202→  .dark {
   203→    --color-background: #0a0a0a;
   204→    --color-foreground: #fafafa;
   205→    --color-primary: #818cf8;
   206→    --color-secondary: #fbbf24;
   207→    --color-accent: #f9a8d4;
   208→    --color-muted: #262626;
   209→    --color-border: #404040;
   210→  }
   211→
   212→  /* Custom themes via data attributes */
   213→  [data-theme='ocean'] {
   214→    --color-primary: #aab9ff;
   215→    --color-secondary: #56d0a0;
   216→  }
   217→
   218→  [data-theme='rainforest'] {
   219→    --color-primary: #56d0a0;
   220→    --color-secondary: #34d399;
   221→  }
   222→
   223→  [data-theme='candy'] {
   224→    --color-primary: #f9a8d4;
   225→    --color-secondary: #fb7185;
   226→  }
   227→}
   228→```
   229→
   230→**Usage in Markup:**
   231→```html
   232→<!-- Automatic utility class generation -->
   233→<div class="bg-primary text-foreground">
   234→  <button class="bg-accent hover:bg-accent/90">Click me</button>
   235→</div>
   236→
   237→<!-- Arbitrary value syntax for theme variables -->
   238→<div class="bg-(--color-primary)"></div>
   239→```
   240→
   241→#### Semantic Color Strategy (Recommended)
   242→
   243→**Role-Based Naming:**
   244→```css
   245→@theme {
   246→  /* Surface colors */
   247→  --color-background: #ffffff;
   248→  --color-surface: #f9fafb;
   249→  --color-surface-elevated: #ffffff;
   250→
   251→  /* Text colors */
   252→  --color-foreground: #171717;
   253→  --color-muted-foreground: #737373;
   254→
   255→  /* Interactive states */
   256→  --color-primary: #3f3cbb;
   257→  --color-primary-hover: #312e81;
   258→  --color-destructive: #dc2626;
   259→  --color-destructive-hover: #b91c1c;
   260→
   261→  /* Borders and dividers */
   262→  --color-border: #e5e5e5;
   263→  --color-input-border: #d4d4d4;
   264→  --color-ring: #3f3cbb; /* Focus rings */
   265→}
   266→```
   267→
   268→**Benefits:**
   269→- Component-agnostic (works across design systems)
   270→- Easy theme switching (override semantic tokens)
   271→- Predictable dark mode (same utility classes, different values)
   272→
   273→---
   274→
   275→## 3. Animation & Motion Systems
   276→
   277→### Centralized Animation Tokens
   278→
   279→**Sources:**
   280→- https://motion.dev/docs/react-tailwind
   281→- https://tailwindcss.com/docs/animation
   282→
   283→#### Architecture Strategy: Tailwind for Static, Motion for Dynamic
   284→
   285→**Key Principle:** Let each library do what it does best:
   286→- **Tailwind:** Static animations (transitions, keyframes)
   287→- **Motion/Vue Animations:** Dynamic, interactive animations (gestures, layout shifts)
   288→
   289→#### Tailwind Animation Configuration
   290→
   291→**Define Animation Tokens:**
   292→```css
   293→@theme {
   294→  /* Animation durations */
   295→  --animate-duration-fast: 150ms;
   296→  --animate-duration-base: 300ms;
   297→  --animate-duration-slow: 500ms;
   298→
   299→  /* Easing functions */
   300→  --ease-in-out: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
   301→  --ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
   302→
   303→  /* Predefined animations */
   304→  --animate-fade-in: fade-in var(--animate-duration-base) var(--ease-in-out);
   305→  --animate-slide-up: slide-up var(--animate-duration-base) var(--ease-in-out);
   306→  --animate-scale-in: scale-in var(--animate-duration-fast) var(--ease-spring);
   307→
   308→  @keyframes fade-in {
   309→    from { opacity: 0; }
   310→    to { opacity: 1; }
   311→  }
   312→
   313→  @keyframes slide-up {
   314→    from {
   315→      opacity: 0;
   316→      transform: translateY(1rem);
   317→    }
   318→    to {
   319→      opacity: 1;
   320→      transform: translateY(0);
   321→    }
   322→  }
   323→
   324→  @keyframes scale-in {
   325→    from {
   326→      opacity: 0;
   327→      transform: scale(0.95);
   328→    }
   329→    to {
   330→      opacity: 1;
   331→      transform: scale(1);
   332→    }
   333→  }
   334→}
   335→```
   336→
   337→**Usage:**
   338→```html
   339→<div class="animate-fade-in">Fades in on load</div>
   340→<div class="animate-slide-up hover:animate-scale-in">Interactive</div>
   341→```
   342→
   343→#### Vue 3 Transition Integration
   344→
   345→**Sources:**
   346→- https://vueschool.io/lessons/custom-vue-transition-classes-aka-tailwind-css-with-vue-transitions
   347→- https://stackoverflow.com/questions/68998731/vue-transition-with-tailwind
   348→
   349→**Pattern: Custom Transition Classes:**
   350→```vue
   351→<template>
   352→  <Transition
   353→    enter-active-class="transition duration-300 ease-out"
   354→    enter-from-class="opacity-0 scale-95"
   355→    enter-to-class="opacity-100 scale-100"
   356→    leave-active-class="transition duration-200 ease-in"
   357→    leave-from-class="opacity-100 scale-100"
   358→    leave-to-class="opacity-0 scale-95"
   359→  >
   360→    <div v-if="show" class="modal">Content</div>
   361→  </Transition>
   362→</template>
   363→```
   364→
   365→**Reusable Composable Pattern:**
   366→```typescript
   367→// composables/useTransitionClasses.ts
   368→export const useTransitionClasses = () => ({
   369→  fadeIn: {
   370→    enterActiveClass: 'transition-opacity duration-300',
   371→    enterFromClass: 'opacity-0',
   372→    enterToClass: 'opacity-100',
   373→    leaveActiveClass: 'transition-opacity duration-200',
   374→    leaveFromClass: 'opacity-100',
   375→    leaveToClass: 'opacity-0',
   376→  },
   377→  slideUp: {
   378→    enterActiveClass: 'transition-all duration-300 ease-out',
   379→    enterFromClass: 'opacity-0 translate-y-4',
   380→    enterToClass: 'opacity-100 translate-y-0',
   381→    leaveActiveClass: 'transition-all duration-200 ease-in',
   382→    leaveFromClass: 'opacity-100 translate-y-0',
   383→    leaveToClass: 'opacity-0 translate-y-4',
   384→  },
   385→});
   386→```
   387→
   388→```vue
   389→<script setup lang="ts">
   390→import { useTransitionClasses } from '@/composables/useTransitionClasses';
   391→
   392→const transitions = useTransitionClasses();
   393→</script>
   394→
   395→<template>
   396→  <Transition v-bind="transitions.fadeIn">
   397→    <div v-if="show">Content</div>
   398→  </Transition>
   399→</template>
   400→```
   401→
   402→#### Responsive Animation Scaling
   403→
   404→**Pattern: CSS Variables + Tailwind Responsive Utilities:**
   405→```css
   406→@theme {
   407→  --animate-duration: 300ms;
   408→}
   409→
   410→@layer base {
   411→  /* Reduce motion on mobile */
   412→  @media (max-width: 640px) {
   413→    :root {
   414→      --animate-duration: 200ms;
   415→    }
   416→  }
   417→
   418→  /* Respect user preferences */
   419→  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
   420→    :root {
   421→      --animate-duration: 0ms;
   422→    }
   423→  }
   424→}
   425→```
   426→
   427→**Vue Composable for Responsive Animations:**
   428→```typescript
   429→// composables/useResponsiveAnimation.ts
   430→import { ref, computed, onMounted } from 'vue';
   431→
   432→export const useResponsiveAnimation = () => {
   433→  const prefersReducedMotion = ref(false);
   434→
   435→  onMounted(() => {
   436→    const mediaQuery = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)');
   437→    prefersReducedMotion.value = mediaQuery.matches;
   438→
   439→    mediaQuery.addEventListener('change', (e) => {
   440→      prefersReducedMotion.value = e.matches;
   441→    });
   442→  });
   443→
   444→  const animationDuration = computed(() => {
   445→    if (prefersReducedMotion.value) return 0;
   446→    return getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)
   447→      .getPropertyValue('--animate-duration');
   448→  });
   449→
   450→  return { animationDuration, prefersReducedMotion };
   451→};
   452→```
   453→
   454→#### Performance Considerations: Web Animations API
   455→
   456→**When to Use:**
   457→- Complex, multi-property animations
   458→- Animations requiring fine-grained control
   459→- Performance-critical animations (runs on compositor thread)
   460→
   461→**Pattern:**
   462→```typescript
   463→// composables/useWebAnimation.ts
   464→export const useWebAnimation = (
   465→  element: Ref<HTMLElement | null>,
   466→  keyframes: Keyframe[],
   467→  options: KeyframeAnimationOptions
   468→) => {
   469→  const animation = ref<Animation | null>(null);
   470→
   471→  const play = () => {
   472→    if (!element.value) return;
   473→
   474→    animation.value = element.value.animate(keyframes, {
   475→      duration: parseInt(
   476→        getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)
   477→          .getPropertyValue('--animate-duration')
   478→      ),
   479→      easing: getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)
   480→        .getPropertyValue('--ease-in-out'),
   481→      ...options,
   482→    });
   483→  };
   484→
   485→  return { play, animation };
   486→};
   487→```
