   491→## 4. Astro + Vue + Tailwind Integration
   492→
   493→### SSR-Safe Tailwind Patterns
   494→
   495→**Sources:**
   496→- https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/styling/
   497→- https://themefisher.com/tailwind-css-with-astro
   498→
   499→#### Setup Configuration
   500→
   501→**Install Tailwind:**
   502→```bash
   503→npx astro add tailwind
   504→```
   505→
   506→**Tailwind Config (`tailwind.config.mjs`):**
   507→```javascript
   508→/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
   509→export default {
   510→  content: [
   511→    './src/**/*.{astro,html,js,jsx,md,mdx,svelte,ts,tsx,vue}'
   512→  ],
   513→  darkMode: 'class', // Critical for SSR compatibility
   514→  theme: {
   515→    extend: {}, // Use CSS @theme instead in v4
   516→  },
   517→  plugins: [],
   518→}
   519→```
   520→
   521→**Global Styles (`src/styles/global.css`):**
   522→```css
   523→@import "tailwindcss";
   524→
   525→@theme {
   526→  /* Custom design tokens */
   527→  --color-brand: #3f3cbb;
   528→  --font-display: Poppins, sans-serif;
   529→}
   530→
   531→@layer base {
   532→  /* Base styles that affect all pages */
   533→  html {
   534→    font-family: var(--font-display);
   535→  }
   536→}
   537→```
   538→
   539→**Layout Component (`src/layouts/Layout.astro`):**
   540→```astro
   541→---
   542→import '../styles/global.css';
   543→
   544→interface Props {
   545→  title: string;
   546→}
   547→
   548→const { title } = Astro.props;
   549→---
   550→
   551→<!doctype html>
   552→<html lang="en">
   553→  <head>
   554→    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
   555→    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
   556→    <title>{title}</title>
   557→  </head>
   558→  <body class="bg-background text-foreground">
   559→    <slot />
   560→  </body>
   561→</html>
   562→```
   563→
   564→#### Dark Mode Implementation (SSR-Safe)
   565→
   566→**Source:** https://namoku.dev/blog/darkmode-tailwind-astro/
   567→
   568→**Critical Pattern: Inline Script for Flash Prevention**
   569→
   570→```astro
   571→---
   572→// src/layouts/Layout.astro
   573→import '../styles/global.css';
   574→---
   575→
   576→<!doctype html>
   577→<html lang="en">
   578→  <head>
   579→    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
   580→    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
   581→    <title>{title}</title>
   582→
   583→    <!-- CRITICAL: Inline script runs before page render -->
   584→    <script is:inline>
   585→      // IIFE to prevent global scope pollution
   586→      (function() {
   587→        const getTheme = () => {
   588→          // Check localStorage first
   589→          if (typeof localStorage !== 'undefined') {
   590→            const stored = localStorage.getItem('theme');
   591→            if (stored) return stored;
   592→          }
   593→
   594→          // Fall back to system preference
   595→          return window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches
   596→            ? 'dark'
   597→            : 'light';
   598→        };
   599→
   600→        const theme = getTheme();
   601→
   602→        // Apply dark class immediately (before render)
   603→        if (theme === 'dark') {
   604→          document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
   605→        }
   606→      })();
   607→    </script>
   608→  </head>
   609→  <body>
   610→    <slot />
   611→  </body>
   612→</html>
   613→```
   614→
   615→**⚠️ Key Point:** The `is:inline` directive prevents Astro from bundling/optimizing the script, ensuring it runs synchronously before page render.
   616→
   617→#### View Transitions Dark Mode Persistence
   618→
   619→**Problem:** Astro View Transitions API replaces DOM content, removing the `dark` class.
   620→
   621→**Solution:**
   622→```astro
   623→<script>
   624→  // Theme toggle logic
   625→  function applyTheme() {
   626→    const theme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';
   627→    document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark', theme === 'dark');
   628→  }
   629→
   630→  function toggleTheme() {
   631→    const currentTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';
   632→    const newTheme = currentTheme === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark';
   633→    localStorage.setItem('theme', newTheme);
   634→    applyTheme();
   635→  }
   636→
   637→  // Apply on initial load
   638→  applyTheme();
   639→
   640→  // Reapply after View Transitions navigation
   641→  document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', () => {
   642→    applyTheme();
   643→
   644→    // Reattach event listeners (removed during swap)
   645→    const themeToggle = document.getElementById('themeToggle');
   646→    if (themeToggle && !themeToggle.hasAttribute('onclick')) {
   647→      themeToggle.addEventListener('click', toggleTheme);
   648→    }
   649→  });
   650→</script>
   651→
   652→<button id="themeToggle" type="button">
   653→  Toggle Theme
   654→</button>
   655→```
   656→
   657→**Event Lifecycle:**
   658→- `astro:before-preparation` - Before new page fetch
   659→- `astro:after-preparation` - After new page fetch
   660→- `astro:before-swap` - Before DOM replacement
   661→- **`astro:after-swap`** - **Use this for theme persistence**
   662→- `astro:page-load` - After navigation complete
   663→
   664→#### Vue Component Tailwind Class Hydration
   665→
   666→**SSR-Safe Pattern:**
   667→```vue
   668→<script setup lang="ts">
   669→import { ref, onMounted } from 'vue';
   670→
   671→// Safe: Static classes (hydrated correctly)
   672→const baseClasses = 'bg-primary text-white px-4 py-2 rounded';
   673→
   674→// Dangerous: Dynamic classes computed during SSR
   675→// const dynamicClasses = computed(() => {
   676→//   return isDark.value ? 'bg-gray-900' : 'bg-white'; // ❌ SSR mismatch
   677→// });
   678→
   679→// Safe: Dynamic classes after mount
   680→const themeClasses = ref('');
   681→
   682→onMounted(() => {
   683→  const theme = localStorage.getItem('theme');
   684→  themeClasses.value = theme === 'dark' ? 'bg-gray-900' : 'bg-white';
   685→});
   686→</script>
   687→
   688→<template>
   689→  <button :class="[baseClasses, themeClasses]">
   690→    Click me
   691→  </button>
   692→</template>
   693→```
   694→
   695→**Alternative: CSS Variable Strategy (Preferred):**
   696→```vue
   697→<script setup lang="ts">
   698→// No JavaScript needed - CSS handles theme reactivity
   699→</script>
   700→
   701→<template>
   702→  <button class="bg-background text-foreground hover:bg-primary">
   703→    Click me
   704→  </button>
   705→</template>
   706→
   707→<style scoped>
   708→/* Tailwind utilities automatically respond to .dark class */
   709→</style>
   710→```
   711→
   712→#### Global Styles Organization
   713→
   714→**Recommended Directory Structure:**
   715→```
   716→src/
   717→├── styles/
   718→│   ├── global.css         # Tailwind imports + @theme
