   792→
   793→## 5. Plugin Architecture
   794→
   795→### When to Create Plugins vs Utilities
   796→
   797→**Source:** https://tailwindcss.com/docs/plugins
   798→
   799→#### Decision Framework
   800→
   801→| Use Case | Solution | Reasoning |
   802→|----------|----------|-----------|
   803→| Single CSS property | `@utility` directive | Simpler, less overhead |
   804→| Multi-property pattern | `@utility` with nesting | Keeps CSS together |
   805→| Complex component base styles | Plugin with `addComponents` | Semantic, reusable |
   806→| New variants (custom selectors) | `@custom-variant` directive | Built-in support in v4 |
   807→| JavaScript-generated utilities | Plugin with `matchUtilities` | Dynamic value generation |
   808→
   809→#### Custom Utilities (Preferred for Most Cases)
   810→
   811→**Simple Utility:**
   812→```css
   813→@utility content-auto {
   814→  content-visibility: auto;
   815→}
   816→
   817→/* Generates: */
   818→.content-auto { content-visibility: auto; }
   819→```
   820→
   821→**Multi-Property Utility:**
   822→```css
   823→@utility scrollbar-hidden {
   824→  &::-webkit-scrollbar {
   825→    display: none;
   826→  }
   827→
   828→  scrollbar-width: none;
   829→}
   830→
   831→/* Generates with variants: */
   832→.scrollbar-hidden::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
   833→.hover\:scrollbar-hidden:hover::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
   834→```
   835→
   836→**Parameterized Utility:**
   837→```css
   838→@utility tab-* {
   839→  tab-size: --value(--tab-size-*);
   840→}
   841→
   842→/* Usage: tab-4, tab-8, tab-[12] */
   843→```
   844→
   845→**Value Function Capabilities:**
   846→```css
   847→@utility leading-* {
   848→  /* Theme matching */
   849→  line-height: --value(--line-height-*);
   850→
   851→  /* Bare values */
   852→  /* --value(integer) - unitless numbers */
   853→  /* --value(percentage) - percentage values */
   854→
   855→  /* Literal values */
   856→  /* --value("inherit", "initial") */
   857→
   858→  /* Arbitrary values */
   859→  /* --value([length], [percentage]) */
   860→}
   861→```
   862→
   863→#### Custom Variants (v4 Pattern)
   864→
   865→**Role-Based Variant:**
   866→```css
   867→@custom-variant theme-midnight {
   868→  &:where([data-theme="midnight"] *) {
   869→    @slot;
   870→  }
   871→}
   872→
   873→/* Usage: theme-midnight:bg-purple-900 */
   874→```
   875→
   876→**State Variant:**
   877→```css
   878→@custom-variant group-loading {
   879→  :merge(.group)[data-loading] & {
   880→    @slot;
   881→  }
   882→}
   883→
   884→/* Usage: group-loading:opacity-50 */
   885→```
   886→
   887→**Media Query Variant:**
   888→```css
   889→@custom-variant motion-safe {
   890→  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
   891→    @slot;
   892→  }
   893→}
   894→
   895→/* Usage: motion-safe:animate-fade-in */
   896→```
   897→
   898→#### Plugin Patterns (v3 and Legacy Support)
   899→
   900→**When to Use Plugins:**
   901→- Supporting Tailwind v3 projects
   902→- Complex JavaScript logic for utility generation
   903→- Third-party libraries/design systems
   904→- Advanced theme manipulation
   905→
   906→**Component Plugin Pattern:**
   907→```javascript
   908→// plugins/components.js
   909→const plugin = require('tailwindcss/plugin');
   910→
   911→module.exports = plugin(function({ addComponents, theme }) {
   912→  addComponents({
   913→    '.card': {
   914→      backgroundColor: theme('colors.white'),
   915→      borderRadius: theme('borderRadius.lg'),
   916→      padding: theme('spacing.6'),
   917→      boxShadow: theme('boxShadow.xl'),
   918→    },
   919→    '.card-dark': {
   920→      backgroundColor: theme('colors.gray.800'),
   921→      color: theme('colors.white'),
   922→    },
   923→  });
   924→});
   925→```
   926→
   927→**Dynamic Utility Plugin:**
   928→```javascript
   929→// plugins/utilities.js
   930→const plugin = require('tailwindcss/plugin');
   931→
   932→module.exports = plugin(function({ matchUtilities, theme }) {
   933→  matchUtilities(
   934→    {
   935→      'grid-cols-fit': (value) => ({
   936→        gridTemplateColumns: `repeat(auto-fit, minmax(${value}, 1fr))`,
   937→      }),
   938→    },
   939→    { values: theme('spacing') }
   940→  );
   941→});
   942→
   943→// Usage: grid-cols-fit-64, grid-cols-fit-[200px]
   944→```
   945→
   946→**Variant Plugin:**
   947→```javascript
   948→// plugins/variants.js
   949→const plugin = require('tailwindcss/plugin');
   950→
   951→module.exports = plugin(function({ addVariant }) {
   952→  addVariant('third', '&:nth-child(3)');
   953→  addVariant('hocus', ['&:hover', '&:focus']);
   954→
   955→  // Complex selector
   956→  addVariant('supports-grid', '@supports (display: grid)');
   957→});
   958→
   959→// Usage: third:font-bold, hocus:underline
   960→```
   961→
   962→#### Plugin File Organization
   963→
   964→**Monolithic (Small Projects):**
   965→```javascript
   966→// tailwind.config.js
   967→module.exports = {
   968→  plugins: [
   969→    require('@tailwindcss/forms'),
   970→    require('./plugins/custom'),
   971→  ],
   972→};
   973→```
   974→
   975→**Modular (Design Systems/Large Projects):**
   976→```
   977→plugins/
   978→├── index.js              # Aggregates all plugins
   979→├── components/
   980→│   ├── buttons.js
   981→│   ├── cards.js
   982→│   └── forms.js
   983→├── utilities/
   984→│   ├── grid.js
   985→│   ├── typography.js
   986→│   └── spacing.js
   987→└── variants/
   988→    ├── states.js
   989→    └── themes.js
   990→```
   991→
   992→```javascript
   993→// plugins/index.js
   994→const components = require('./components');
   995→const utilities = require('./utilities');
   996→const variants = require('./variants');
   997→
   998→module.exports = [
   999→  components,
  1000→  utilities,
  1001→  variants,
  1002→];
  1003→
  1004→// tailwind.config.js
  1005→module.exports = {
  1006→  plugins: require('./plugins'),
  1007→};
  1008→```
  1009→
  1010→---
  1011→
  1012→## 6. Design System Examples & Industry Patterns
  1013→
  1014→### Shadcn/UI Approach (CSS Variables + Semantic Naming)
  1015→
  1016→**Pattern:** Define all colors as CSS variables, use semantic utility classes
  1017→
  1018→```css
  1019→@layer base {
  1020→  :root {
  1021→    --background: 0 0% 100%;
  1022→    --foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  1023→    --card: 0 0% 100%;
  1024→    --card-foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  1025→    --primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
  1026→    --primary-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1027→    --destructive: 0 84.2% 60.2%;
  1028→    --destructive-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1029→    --radius: 0.5rem;
  1030→  }
  1031→
  1032→  .dark {
  1033→    --background: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  1034→    --foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1035→    --card: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
  1036→    --card-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1037→    --primary: 210 40% 98%;
  1038→    --primary-foreground: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
  1039→    --destructive: 0 62.8% 30.6%;
  1040→    --destructive-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  1041→  }
  1042→}
  1043→
  1044→@layer base {
  1045→  * {
  1046→    @apply border-border;
  1047→  }
  1048→  body {
  1049→    @apply bg-background text-foreground;
  1050→  }
  1051→}
  1052→```
  1053→
  1054→**Benefits:**
  1055→- Theme switching via CSS variable override
  1056→- HSL format allows opacity modifiers: `bg-primary/50`
  1057→- Semantic names survive redesigns
  1058→
  1059→### Radix UI/Headless UI Pattern (Unstyled Components + Tailwind)
  1060→
  1061→**Pattern:** Headless components with Tailwind styling via props
  1062→
  1063→```vue
  1064→<script setup lang="ts">
  1065→import { Dialog, DialogPanel, DialogTitle } from '@headlessui/vue';
  1066→
  1067→const isOpen = ref(false);
  1068→</script>
  1069→
  1070→<template>
  1071→  <Dialog
  1072→    :open="isOpen"
  1073→    @close="isOpen = false"
  1074→    class="relative z-50"
  1075→  >
  1076→    <!-- Backdrop -->
  1077→    <div class="fixed inset-0 bg-black/30" aria-hidden="true" />
  1078→
  1079→    <!-- Panel -->
  1080→    <div class="fixed inset-0 flex items-center justify-center p-4">
  1081→      <DialogPanel class="mx-auto max-w-sm rounded bg-white p-6 shadow-xl">
  1082→        <DialogTitle class="text-lg font-medium">
  1083→          Deactivate account
  1084→        </DialogTitle>
  1085→        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">
  1086→          Are you sure you want to deactivate your account?
  1087→        </p>
  1088→        <div class="mt-4 flex gap-2">
  1089→          <button
  1090→            class="btn-primary"
  1091→            @click="isOpen = false"
  1092→          >
  1093→            Deactivate
  1094→          </button>
  1095→          <button
  1096→            class="btn-secondary"
  1097→            @click="isOpen = false"
  1098→          >
  1099→            Cancel
  1100→          </button>
  1101→        </div>
  1102→      </DialogPanel>
  1103→    </div>
  1104→  </Dialog>
  1105→</template>
  1106→```
  1107→
  1108→**Benefits:**
  1109→- Accessibility built-in (focus management, ARIA)
  1110→- Full styling control via Tailwind
  1111→- No CSS conflicts or specificity issues
  1112→
  1113→---
  1114→
  1115→## 7. Key Takeaways & Action Items
  1116→
  1117→### Immediate Implementation Steps
  1118→
  1119→1. **Migrate to Tailwind v4 CSS Configuration**
  1120→   - Replace `tailwind.config.js` theme with `@theme` directive
  1121→   - Define semantic color tokens with dark mode variants
  1122→   - Use `@utility` for custom utilities instead of plugins
  1123→
  1124→2. **Implement SSR-Safe Dark Mode**
  1125→   - Use `is:inline` script in Astro layout for flash prevention
  1126→   - Add `astro:after-swap` listener for View Transitions persistence
  1127→   - Store theme preference in localStorage with system fallback
  1128→
  1129→3. **Centralize Animation System**
  1130→   - Define animation tokens via `@theme` (durations, easings, keyframes)
  1131→   - Create Vue composables for Transition class sets
  1132→   - Implement `prefers-reduced-motion` checks
  1133→
  1134→4. **Organize Global Styles**
  1135→   - Single import in layout component (`src/styles/global.css`)
  1136→   - Use `@layer base` for element defaults
  1137→   - Use `@layer components` for reusable patterns
  1138→   - Use `@layer utilities` for custom utility classes
  1139→
  1140→5. **Adopt Semantic Color Naming**
  1141→   - Replace literal names (`blue-500`) with role-based (`primary`, `foreground`)
  1142→   - Define dark mode as CSS variable overrides
  1143→   - Use HSL format for opacity modifier support
  1144→
  1145→### Anti-Patterns to Avoid
  1146→
  1147→❌ **Don't:** Compute Tailwind classes dynamically during SSR
  1148→```vue
  1149→<!-- Bad: SSR hydration mismatch -->
  1150→<div :class="isDark ? 'bg-gray-900' : 'bg-white'">
  1151→```
  1152→
  1153→✅ **Do:** Use CSS variables for theme reactivity
  1154→```vue
  1155→<!-- Good: CSS handles reactivity -->
  1156→<div class="bg-background">
  1157→```
  1158→
  1159→---
  1160→
  1161→❌ **Don't:** Import global styles in Vue components
  1162→```vue
  1163→<script setup lang="ts">
  1164→import '@/styles/global.css'; // ❌ Duplicates
  1165→</script>
  1166→```
  1167→
  1168→✅ **Do:** Import once in Astro layout
  1169→```astro
  1170→---
  1171→import '../styles/global.css'; // ✅ Single import
  1172→---
  1173→```
  1174→
  1175→---
  1176→
  1177→❌ **Don't:** Create plugins for simple utilities
  1178→```javascript
  1179→// Over-engineered
  1180→plugin(({ addUtilities }) => {
  1181→  addUtilities({ '.content-auto': { 'content-visibility': 'auto' } });
  1182→});
  1183→```
  1184→
  1185→✅ **Do:** Use `@utility` directive
  1186→```css
  1187→@utility content-auto {
  1188→  content-visibility: auto;
  1189→}
  1190→```
  1191→
  1192→---
  1193→
  1194→❌ **Don't:** Use `theme` to override (removes defaults)
  1195→```javascript
  1196→module.exports = {
  1197→  theme: {
  1198→    colors: { primary: '#3f3cbb' } // ❌ Removes all default colors
  1199→  }
  1200→}
  1201→```
  1202→
  1203→✅ **Do:** Use `@theme` to extend
  1204→```css
  1205→@theme {
  1206→  --color-primary: #3f3cbb; /* ✅ Adds to defaults */
  1207→}
  1208→```
  1209→
  1210→### Performance Optimizations
  1211→
  1212→1. **Purge Unused Styles**
  1213→   - Ensure `content` array includes all template files
  1214→   - Use PurgeCSS safelist for dynamic classes
  1215→
  1216→2. **Minimize CSS Variable Lookups**
  1217→   - Use `@theme inline` when referencing other variables
  1218→   - Avoid deeply nested variable references
  1219→
  1220→3. **Optimize Animations**
  1221→   - Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
  1222→   - Use `will-change` sparingly (only during animation)
  1223→   - Prefer `transform` and `opacity` for GPU acceleration
  1224→
  1225→4. **Code Splitting**
  1226→   - Import component-specific styles via dynamic imports
  1227→   - Use Astro's built-in CSS bundling for critical styles
  1228→
